-- WS-2 fixture: A3/computed — the SOUNDNESS guard.
-- The URL is COMPUTED (`base ++ userInput`), not a literal, so even with α
-- seeded by the outer-body `let dest = …`, α descends into the `++` and finds the
-- LEFT operand is a let-bound EVar whose RHS is itself non-literal (a parameter),
-- so the known prefix is UNKNOWN → ⊤.  Must STAY REJECTED under any concrete
-- wildcard policy.  This guards against α ever recovering a prefix it cannot
-- actually prove — WS-2 only turns over-rejections into acceptances, never the
-- reverse.
effect Net Prefix

extern netGet : String -> <Net _> String

transform userInput =
  let dest = userInput
  (u => netGet dest)
